  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">We can speak of each of these sins in two ways. On one way we may consider the species of either sin , and thus the more a vice is at variance with the opposite virtue the more grievous it is. Now the virtue of friendship has a greater tendency to please than</data>
